interfaces.label: ChangedDeprecatedPaths
description: List of config paths changed during deprecation.

interfaces.label: ConfigDeprecationCommand
description: Outcome of deprecation operation. Allows mutating config values in a declarative way.

interfaces.label: ConfigDeprecationContext
description: Deprecation context provided to {@link ConfigDeprecation | config deprecations}

children.label: version
description: The current Kibana version, e.g `7.16.1`, `8.0.0`

children.label: branch
description: The current Kibana branch, e.g `7.x`, `7.16`, `master`

children.label: docLinks
description: Allow direct access to the doc links from the deprecation handler

interfaces.label: ConfigDeprecationFactory

children.label: deprecate
description:
Deprecate a configuration property from inside a plugin's configuration path.
Will log a deprecation warning if the deprecatedKey was found.

children.label: deprecateFromRoot
description:
Deprecate a configuration property from the root configuration.
Will log a deprecation warning if the deprecatedKey was found.

This should be only used when deprecating properties from different configuration's path.
To deprecate properties from inside a plugin's configuration, use 'deprecate' instead.

children.label: rename
description:
Rename a configuration property from inside a plugin's configuration path.
Will log a deprecation warning if the oldKey was found and deprecation applied.

children.label: renameFromRoot
description:
Rename a configuration property from the root configuration.
Will log a deprecation warning if the oldKey was found and deprecation applied.

This should be only used when renaming properties from different configuration's path.
To rename properties from inside a plugin's configuration, use 'rename' instead.

children.label: unused
description:
Remove a configuration property from inside a plugin's configuration path.
Will log a deprecation warning if the unused key was found and deprecation applied.

children.label: unusedFromRoot
description:
Remove a configuration property from the root configuration.
Will log a deprecation warning if the unused key was found and deprecation applied.

This should be only used when removing properties from outside of a plugin's configuration.
To remove properties from inside a plugin's configuration, use 'unused' instead.

interfaces.label: DeprecatedConfigDetails
description: Deprecated Config Details

children.label: configPath
description: The path of the deprecated config setting

children.label: title
description: The title to be displayed for the deprecation.

children.label: message
description: The message to be displayed for the deprecation.

children.label: level
description:
levels:
- warning: will not break deployment upon upgrade
- critical: needs to be addressed before upgrade.

children.label: silent
description: (optional) set to `true` to prevent the config service from logging the deprecation message.

children.label: documentationUrl
description: (optional) link to the documentation for more details on the deprecation.

children.label: correctiveActions
description: corrective action needed to fix this deprecation.
